                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client with a history of myasthenia gravis presents at a clinic with bilateral ptosis and is drooling, and myasthenic crisis is suspected. The nurse assesses the client for which precipitating factor?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMyasthenic crisis often is caused by undermedication and responds to the administration of cholinergic medications. Cholinergic crisis (the opposite problem) is caused by excess medication and responds to withholding of medications. Too little exercise and excessive fatty food intake are incorrect. Overexertion and overeating possibly could trigger myasthenic crisis.",
                        "id": "13ee6b6351ce482daf68ee3f0bc9f07a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "98ccfbb8eda745868e9984b736fab1d0",
                                "content": "Monitor the chest tube drainage."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "fd8718bef59e47ddb28720244052a52d",
                                "content": "Restrict visitors for 24 hours postoperatively."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "44b30bddda8e4dfaa71c7fdd8de2175e",
                                "content": "Maintain intravenous infusion of lactated Ringer's solution."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "75d23110dd1442ecbe93b17090dc939b",
                                "content": "Avoid administering pain medication to prevent respiratory depression."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "98ccfbb8eda745868e9984b736fab1d0",
                                    "content": "Monitor the chest tube drainage."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
