                        "content": "A thymectomy accomplished via a median sternotomy approach is performed in a client with a diagnosis of myasthenia gravis. The nurse creates a postoperative plan of care for the client that would include which intervention?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "49d86bb4d5071eb7de614d6c79f7abfb",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Creating创新",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe thymus has played a role in the development of myasthenia gravis. A thymectomy is the surgical removal of the thymus gland and may be used for management of clients with myasthenia gravis to improve weakness. The procedure is performed through a median sternotomy or a transcervical approach. Postoperatively the client will have a chest tube in the mediastinum. Lactated intravenous solutions usually are avoided because they can increase weakness. Pain medication is administered as needed, but the client is monitored closely for respiratory depression. There is no reason to restrict visitors.",
                        "id": "2b5ae30ab28d409bad6bac53c3315315",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d67bf42f885f488298a4970c6c98135c",
                                "content": "Here's the MedicAlert bracelet I obtained."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8434317a026b48c3a0daa82ac4039d33",
                                "content": "I need to take my medications an hour before mealtime."
