                        "content": "A client with myasthenia gravis arrives at the hospital emergency department in suspected crisis. The primary health care provider plans to administer edrophonium to differentiate between myasthenic and cholinergic crises. The nurse ensures that which medication is available in the event that the client is in cholinergic crisis?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nClients with cholinergic crisis have experienced an overdosage of medication. Edrophonium will exacerbate symptoms in cholinergic crisis to the point at which the client may need intubation and mechanical ventilation. Intravenous atropine sulfate is used to reverse the effects of these anticholinesterase medications. Morphine sulfate and pyridostigmine bromide would worsen the symptoms of cholinergic crisis. Protamine sulfate is the antidote for heparin.",
                        "id": "9e98bdf84f62414795b2412db891045b",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "42aaa5c84331dbddaeb5b7e19b9f2614",
                                "content": "I will rest each afternoon after my walk."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "23c3b29fc270471b8728dbc6db9a05b0",
                                "content": "I should cough and deep-breathe many times during the day."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "fa7c4a71171b12d8dd64945a2d5ca70c",
                                "content": "I can change the time of my medication on the mornings when I feel strong."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "411b325b7c712221dd916c95ab2d388e",
                                "content": "If I get abdominal cramps and diarrhea, I should call my health care provider."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "42aaa5c84331dbddaeb5b7e19b9f2614",
