                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The home health nurse is visiting a client with myasthenia gravis and is discussing methods to minimize the risk of aspiration during meals related to decreased muscle strength. Which suggestions would the nurse give to the client? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe client avoids swallowing any type of food or drink with the head lifted upward, which could actually cause aspiration by opening the glottis. The client needs to be advised to sit upright while eating, not to talk with food in the mouth (talking requires opening the glottis), to cut food into very small pieces, to chew thoroughly, and to tip the chin downward to swallow.",
